Singer Akothee's sister Cebbie Nyasego yesterday narrated how she was left scared after being robbed at gunpoint. Cebbie took to social media to share the incident that happened in the wee hours of the night in Chiromo, Nairobi. "Oh! Sh!t! Got robbed at gunpoint hapo Chiromo on that bump when the car slowed down and managed to escape with my phone,"Â she wrote. This is not the first case of celebrities being robbed in the city. Journalist Shiksha Arora narrated a harrowing ordeal she went through at the hands of robbers around Globe Roundabout in Nairobi CBD last year. She explained how three thugs worked together and attempted to steal her belongings. Following her experience, Shiksha warned that the thugs work in teams to steal in broad daylight.